actually we need a lot of help. And I'll try

00:03:24.981 --> 00:03:28.049
and explain why.

00:03:28.049 --> 00:03:33.069
So in schools today across our country, we're
really in an age of accountability. There's

00:03:33.069 --> 00:03:39.969
such a strong focus on meeting standards through
No Child Left Behind and even through ESEA,

00:03:39.969 --> 00:03:44.020
which is followed up with No Child Left Behind.

00:03:44.020 --> 00:03:50.909
The emphasis is-is not on creative and learning
environments or giving spaces for problem

00:03:50.909 --> 00:03:54.799
solving. The emphasis is on closing achievement
gaps.

00:03:54.799 --> 00:04:01.470
So if students don't perform at certain levels
on tests, then the focus is helping those

00:04:01.470 --> 00:04:06.099
students get to that level. So what you test
is what you get.

00:04:06.099 --> 00:04:10.620
It's created an emergence of collaborative
learning environments for-for teachers which

00:04:10.620 --> 00:04:15.580
is actually terrific 'cause teachers are less
isolated than they used to be, but again the

00:04:15.580 --> 00:04:21.040
focus is really on can they meet the base
standard.

00:04:21.040 --> 00:04:27.010
Now those people who poke at No Child Left
Behind -- actually the Chesapeake Bay Foundation

00:04:27.010 --> 00:04:33.500
created No Child Left Inside, which is a way
of a grass roots movements of getting students

00:04:33.500 --> 00:04:36.840
outdoors and-and connected to their environment.

00:04:36.840 --> 00:04:43.120
Here's a picture of our students in a project,
a research based project in a pond that looks

00:04:43.120 --> 00:04:47.780
at the different characteristics that will
influence salamander migration.

00:04:47.780 --> 00:04:57.000
